==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Old French [[reaume]] (modern [[royaume]]), from the participle stem of Latin [[regare]] ‘rule’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/rɛlm/}}
*{{AHD|rĕlm}}, {{SAMPA|/relm/}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɛlm|Rhymes: -ɛlm]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[kingdom]] ''(now mainly in Law)''; a [[territory]] or [[state]], as [[ruled]] by a specific power.
# A [[sphere]] of [[activity]] or [[influence]]; a [[field]], [[domain]] or [[province]].

